_source.productName: Queensland University Musical Society presents - Home: a memoir in movements
_source.productDescription:
QUMS is proud to present their  Semester 1, 2025 Concert, Home - a memoir in movements, conducted by Guillaume Lemay-Yates and accompanied by Jerica Lau, performing a selection of music representing feelings of home, love and obscure sorrows.

The concert features the world premiere of Ravens by Evangelynne Ennis and Preface by Cloud Tan, as well as the Australian Premiere of Andr√© van der Merwe's arrangement of Bright Blue's Weeping and Kenneth Tay's A Summer Full of Flowers.

They'll rounding out the repertoire with some new choir favourites by household names such as Ysaye Barnwell and Astrid Jorgensen. 

The concert will be held in the GHD Auditorium, which is inside the Advanced Engineering Building (49) at The University of Queensland, St Lucia. 

UQ is very accessible by public transport, bicycle, or car. The best parking is the Grassy Knoll car park (P11) or on Sir William MacGregor Drive near-by. A limited number of accessible car parks are available closer to the building. For more info on accessible parking, see the UQ website.

_source.productName: Expressing Compassion and Love through Art
_source.productDescription:
Join them in the beautiful surroundings of Montville County Cabins, Montville in a full day workshop with award-winning artist HyunHee Lee.

Participants will be encouraged to create artworks using personally chosen fragments of words and writings cut out of silk before stitching them onto canvas. These fragments will be reassembled and stitched onto canvas creating new stories and opening insights into new possibilities. During this process they will have the experience of connecting with their emotions and feelings which will be developed and express through their individual artworks. 

Each participant will complete one personalised artwork. All materials will be supplied, and morning tea and lunch are included in the cost.

Bergabunglah dengan mereka di lingkungan yang indah di Montville County Cabins, Montville dalam lokakarya sehari penuh dengan seniman pemenang penghargaan HyunHee Lee.

Peserta akan didorong untuk membuat karya seni menggunakan potongan kata-kata dan tulisan yang dipilih sendiri yang dipotong dari sutra sebelum dijahit ke kanvas. Potongan-potongan ini akan disusun kembali dan dijahit ke kanvas untuk menciptakan cerita baru dan membuka wawasan tentang kemungkinan-kemungkinan baru. Selama proses ini, mereka akan memiliki pengalaman terhubung dengan emosi dan perasaan mereka yang akan dikembangkan dan diekspresikan melalui karya seni masing-masing.

Setiap peserta akan menyelesaikan satu karya seni yang dipersonalisasi. Semua bahan akan disediakan, dan teh pagi serta makan siang sudah termasuk dalam biaya.

_source.productDescription:
Spend time in the east and discover the 'spirit of the mountain' at Cauldron Distillery. The event opens with a welcome from the Wangeriburra peoples, the traditional owners of Jambreen or Tamborine Mountain. Hear the stories of their ancestors as they set the scene for this relaxed afternoon of storytelling and song. 

As the sun goes down, graze on delicious dishes from the Cauldron kitchen made with locally sourced produce and ingredients. Enjoy live performances from legendary Australian artist Ben Lee and other talented local musicians, all while sipping on Cauldron's exceptional range of locally produced spirits. On this opening weekend, we invite you to soak up the spirit of Tamborine Mountain with family and friends, taking in stunning mountain views and the finest local flavours.

Spirit of the Mountain is deliciously presented as part of the 2025 Scenic Rim Eat Local Month.

Hills Carnivale brings to a close four weeks of incredible events as part of the Hills Festival. The annual Hills Carnivale on Saturday 31 May at George Willmore Park is a free entry event with a whole host of activities for little kids and big kids alike.

Whether you've dedicated countless hours to a cause close to your heart, or you've been touched by the kindness of a volunteer in your community, this celebration is for you!

Live entertainment on a huge stage
Jumping castle, face painting, petting zoo
Food trucks, market stalls
Chess championship, games and activities
Volunteering awards
Meet with groups and organisations who make our community a better place
Stunning laser show at sundown and more!

So mark your calendars, spread the word, and come make this a celebration to remember!
Free for all! Everyone is welcome.

This event is proudly sponsored by Redland City Council.

_source.productName: The Sunset Run: Chase The Stars
_source.productDescription:
The Sunset Run is returning for its fourth year with Chase The Stars, rolling out a $20 million luxury supercar convoy forming a public spectacle at Oracle Boulevard  on Saturday 31 May.

Founded by Her Supercar Life (HSL), Rachael Reid, The Sunset Run has cemented itself as a standout luxury automotive experience in Southeast Queensland, now entering its sixth instalment.

'This year's line-up is our most exciting yet with some incredibly unique cars joining us on show, including a newly launched Rolls-Royce making its first public appearance fresh off the back of its global reveal at the Sanctuary Cove Boat Show.

The Oracle Boulevard shutdown is also set to return.

'The Oracle Boulevard shutdown has become a real highlight of the day - last year, crowds had already started gathering before the cars arrived and they can't wait to bring that excitement back again,' says Rachael.

As the luxury convoy sets out across the Gold Coast, the real engine behind the Sunset Run is to drive purpose as it raises funds for Make-A-Wish Foundation.

Chase The Stars is sponsored by Castle Property Agents and CorpSure, and partners include Tiffany & Co. and Ralph Lauren.

Event-goers can expect a lineup of Australia's most prestigious and exotic supercars including Lamborghinis, Ferraris, Aston Martins, McLaren, Rolls-Royce and more.

Sunset Run kembali untuk tahun keempatnya bersama Chase The Stars, menggelar konvoi mobil mewah seharga $20 juta yang menjadi tontonan publik di Oracle Boulevard pada Sabtu, 31 Mei.

Didirikan oleh Her Supercar Life (HSL), Rachael Reid, The Sunset Run telah mengukuhkan dirinya sebagai pengalaman otomotif mewah yang menonjol di Queensland Tenggara, kini memasuki edisi keenamnya.

'Tahun ini, rangkaian acara kami adalah yang paling menarik dengan beberapa mobil yang sangat unik yang ikut serta dalam acara, termasuk Rolls-Royce yang baru diluncurkan dan tampil pertama kali di depan publik setelah peluncuran globalnya di Sanctuary Cove Boat Show.

Penutupan Oracle Boulevard juga akan kembali.

'Penutupan Oracle Boulevard telah menjadi sorotan utama hari itu - tahun lalu, kerumunan orang sudah mulai berkumpul sebelum mobil-mobil datang dan mereka tidak sabar untuk menghadirkan kembali kegembiraan itu,' kata Rachael.

Saat konvoi mewah tersebut berangkat melintasi Gold Coast, mesin sebenarnya di balik Sunset Run adalah untuk menggerakkan tujuan saat mengumpulkan dana untuk Make-A-Wish Foundation.

Chase The Stars disponsori oleh Castle Property Agents dan CorpSure, dan mitranya termasuk Tiffany & Co. dan Ralph Lauren.

Pengunjung acara dapat mengharapkan jajaran mobil super paling bergengsi dan eksotis di Australia termasuk Lamborghini, Ferrari, Aston Martin, McLaren, Rolls-Royce, dan banyak lagi.

_source.productName: Totems  and trinkets Colour Melts Hot Glass workshop
_source.productDescription:
In your fused glass workshop you will explore combinations of coloured glass- learning Glass cutting and chipping.

Using embellishments such as glass caviar, rods, stringers, dots, frit (fine sand like glass) and shards of colour you can make your creative masterpieces. You are free to explore your own style with guidance from our award winning glass artist Kaylene Higgs.

Once your finished project has been through the kiln firing process you can turn them into magnets, jewellery, Suncatchers totems and trinkets. There are so many possibilities.

A perfect introduction to glass fusing, this workshop gives you all the guidance you need and all the freedom you desire to explore a smorgasbord of glass colours and elements such as stringers, rods, dots, glass caviar, frit and chips.

These are then kiln fired at high temperature, melted to form puddles of colour- each one so totally unique. There is a multitude of colour and pattern combinations  you can use to create an array of colourful and unique gems that you can turn into pendants, earrings, rings or brooches.

There is time to try a few different techniques to give you a good understanding of how glass reacts in the kiln to form random patterns of melted colour.

Dalam lokakarya kaca lebur Anda, Anda akan menjelajahi kombinasi kaca berwarna - mempelajari pemotongan dan pengelupasan kaca.

Menggunakan hiasan seperti kaviar kaca, batang, tali pengikat, titik, frit (pasir halus seperti kaca) dan pecahan warna, Anda dapat membuat karya kreatif Anda sendiri. Anda bebas menjelajahi gaya Anda sendiri dengan bimbingan dari seniman kaca pemenang penghargaan kami Kaylene Higgs.

Setelah proyek Anda yang sudah selesai melalui proses pembakaran di tungku, Anda dapat mengubahnya menjadi magnet, perhiasan, totem Suncatchers, dan pernak-pernik. Ada begitu banyak kemungkinan.

Sebagai pengantar yang sempurna untuk peleburan kaca, lokakarya ini memberi Anda semua panduan yang Anda butuhkan dan semua kebebasan yang Anda inginkan untuk menjelajahi berbagai macam warna dan elemen kaca seperti tali pengikat, batang, titik, kaviar kaca, frit, dan serpihan.

Ini kemudian dibakar di tungku pada suhu tinggi, dicairkan untuk membentuk genangan warna - masing-masing sangat unik. Ada banyak kombinasi warna dan pola yang dapat Anda gunakan untuk membuat berbagai macam permata berwarna-warni dan unik yang dapat Anda ubah menjadi liontin, anting-anting, cincin, atau bros.

Ada waktu untuk mencoba beberapa teknik berbeda untuk memberi Anda pemahaman yang baik tentang bagaimana kaca bereaksi dalam tungku untuk membentuk pola acak dari warna yang meleleh.

_source.productName: An Afternoon with the Artists: 'Come Stay a While' Official Exhibition Opening
_source.productDescription:
Join in to celebrate the official opening of 'Come Stay a While ‚Äì where trees do the talking', a dual exhibition by Louise Corke and Petra Daecke. Enjoy an afternoon of art and insight with guest speaker Bruce Griffiths, a poetry reading by Daecke, and a live pastel demonstration by Corke.  

'Come Stay a While' invites visitors to reflect on their personal connection with nature through soft pastel works that honour the quiet strength and beauty of trees. Guest speaker Bruce Griffiths is a practicing artist and respected tutor based in Kleinton, QLD, renowned for his expressive watercolours and sought-after workshops across Australia. Enjoy this inspiring afternoon with light refreshments provided.

This event is free and all ages are welcome, for catering purposes please RSVP via the website.

'Come Stay a While ‚Äì where trees do the talking' will be exhibited at the Warwick Art Gallery from 29 May until 5 July 2025.

About the Exhibition: 
An exhibition where you will be immersed in nature, to experience visual stories and the pure joy of trees to feel a sense of connection, healing, peace and wholeness. The exhibition showcases each artist's relationship with trees, inviting audience exploration and contemplation.
_source.productShortDescription: Join in to celebrate the official opening of 'Come Stay a While ‚Äì where trees do the talking'.

Bergabunglah untuk merayakan pembukaan resmi 'Come Stay a While ‚Äì where trees do the talking', pameran ganda oleh Louise Corke dan Petra Daecke. Nikmati sore hari yang penuh seni dan wawasan dengan pembicara tamu Bruce Griffiths, pembacaan puisi oleh Daecke, dan demonstrasi pastel langsung oleh Corke. 

'Come Stay a While' mengundang pengunjung untuk merenungkan hubungan pribadi mereka dengan alam melalui karya pastel lembut yang menghargai kekuatan dan keindahan pohon yang tenang. Pembicara tamu Bruce Griffiths adalah seniman yang berpraktik dan tutor yang disegani yang tinggal di Kleinton, QLD, terkenal karena cat airnya yang ekspresif dan lokakarya yang dicari di seluruh Australia. Nikmati sore yang menginspirasi ini dengan minuman ringan yang disediakan.

Acara ini gratis dan semua usia dipersilakan, untuk keperluan katering, silakan konfirmasi kehadiran melalui situs web.

'Come Stay a While ‚Äì where trees do the talking' akan dipamerkan di Warwick Art Gallery mulai 29 Mei hingga 5 Juli 2025.

Tentang Pameran: 
Pameran tempat Anda akan tenggelam dalam alam, untuk mengalami kisah visual dan kegembiraan murni dari pepohonan untuk merasakan rasa keterhubungan, penyembuhan, kedamaian, dan keutuhan. Pameran ini menampilkan hubungan setiap seniman dengan pepohonan, yang mengundang eksplorasi dan kontemplasi dari para pengunjung.

_source.productDescription:
The tides are high but they're holding on!

Due to the effects of Cyclone Alfred and some incredibly high tides SeaFire is changing this year - for community safety. 

For the first time you'll be able to view the same spectacular international fireworks competition from not one location, but four! 

Surfers Paradise foreshore
Broadbeach 
Broadwater Parklands 
HOTA Parklands 

The show has been modified so you can now see it in each of the four locations, at the one time of 7pm! 

The 18-minute show will showcase the two international competitors Belgium and USA and culminate with a spectacular Aussie fireworks finale. 

SeaFire is a free family friendly event and is presented by City of Gold Coast.

For more information search SeaFire 2025 on Facebook or visit the website.

_source.productDescription:
The Sweet Days Hot Nights Festival celebrates the essence of the Burdekin region, renowned as the Sugarcane Capital of Australia, by showcasing its people, produce and culture.

Consisting of two headline events, the Sweet Days Hot Nights Festival starts with the Burdekin Cultural Fair featuring First Fire on Friday night, followed by the Australian Hand Cane Cutting Championships on Saturday at the Home Hill Showgrounds. 

The Burdekin Cultural Fair featuring First Fire celebrates the diversity of the Burdekin region bringing together a diverse range of cultures through a variety of culinary delights, interactive activities and captivating entertainment. Don't miss the highlight of the night, the lighting of the first fire of the 2025 sugarcane crushing season. Hear the crackling of the crop burning, smell the sweet essence of the burning sugar and feel the heat of the fire as it tears through the paddock. 

The Australian Hand Cane Cutting Championships is the ultimate test of skill and endurance, with competitors swinging their cane knives in hopes to be crowned the Australian Hand Cane Cutting Champion! Spectators will have the opportunity to walk through a paddock of burnt sugarcane, immersing themselves in the dirty, back-breaking work of a by-gone era. This family-friendly event promises great food, live music, captivating entertainment and so much more!

_source.productDescription:
Queensland's premier chorus, the Queensland Choir presents a stunning programme of timeless Baroque masterpieces in the historic Concert Hall of the Old Museum Building. 

Together with the Sinfonia of St Andrew's and guest soloists  Annika Hinrichs (soprano) and Morgan Rosati (mezzo-soprano) they will perform some of the most popular and spectacular music by three of the greatest composers of all time - JS Bach, Handel and Vivaldi - that perfectly demonstrates the vitality, elegance, grandeur and dramatic power of the Baroque era.

Programme:
Handel: Sinfonia -  Arrival of the Queen of Sheba (from Solomon)
Handel: Zadok the Priest (Coronation Anthem No.1)
Handel: The King Shall Rejoice (Coronation Anthem No.3)
Bach: Brandenburg Concerto No.3
Bach: Jesu, joy of man's desiring (from Cantata No.147)
Vivaldi: Gloria in D major RV.589

This will be Kevin Power's, last concert as he retires as our conductors with more than 50 years service with the choir.    A very special event and not to be missed.

productComments.commentText:
Queensland's premier chorus, the Queensland Choir presents a stunning programme of timeless Baroque masterpieces in the historic Concert Hall of the Old Museum Building. 

Together with the Sinfonia of St Andrew's and guest soloists  Annika Hinrichs (soprano) and Morgan Rosati (mezzo-soprano) they will perform some of the most popular and spectacular music by three of the greatest composers of all time - JS Bach, Handel and Vivaldi - that perfectly demonstrates the vitality, elegance, grandeur and dramatic power of the Baroque era.

Programme:
Handel: Sinfonia -  Arrival of the Queen of Sheba (from Solomon)
Handel: Zadok the Priest (Coronation Anthem No.1)
Handel: The King Shall Rejoice (Coronation Anthem No.3)
Bach: Brandenburg Concerto No.3
Bach: Jesu, joy of man's desiring (from Cantata No.147)
Vivaldi: Gloria in D major RV.589

This will be Kevin Power's, last concert as he retires as our conductors with more than 50 years service with the choir.    A very special event and not to be missed.

Paduan suara utama Queensland, Queensland Choir mempersembahkan program yang memukau berupa karya-karya Barok yang tak lekang oleh waktu di Aula Konser bersejarah di Old Museum Building.

Bersama dengan Sinfonia of St Andrew's dan solois tamu Annika Hinrichs (soprano) dan Morgan Rosati (mezzo-soprano), mereka akan membawakan beberapa musik paling populer dan spektakuler dari tiga komposer terhebat sepanjang masa - JS Bach, Handel, dan Vivaldi - yang dengan sempurna menunjukkan vitalitas, keanggunan, kemegahan, dan kekuatan dramatis era Barok.

Program:
Handel: Sinfonia - Kedatangan Ratu Sheba (dari Solomon)
Handel: Zadok sang Imam (Lagu Penobatan No.1)
Handel: Sang Raja Akan Bersukacita (Lagu Penobatan No.3)
Bach: Konser Brandenburg No.3
Bach: Jesu, sukacita yang diinginkan manusia (dari Kantata No.147)
Vivaldi: Gloria dalam D mayor RV.589

Ini akan menjadi konser terakhir Kevin Power karena ia pensiun sebagai konduktor kami dengan lebih dari 50 tahun pengabdian di paduan suara. Sebuah acara yang sangat istimewa dan tidak boleh dilewatkan.

Il Queensland Choir, il coro pi√π importante del Queensland, presenta uno straordinario programma di capolavori barocchi senza tempo nella storica Sala Concerti dell'Old Museum Building.

Insieme alla Sinfonia di Sant'Andrea e alle soliste ospiti Annika Hinrichs (soprano) e Morgan Rosati (mezzosoprano), eseguiranno alcune delle musiche pi√π popolari e spettacolari di tre dei pi√π grandi compositori di tutti i tempi - J.S. Bach, H√§ndel e Vivaldi - che dimostrano perfettamente la vitalit√†, l'eleganza, la grandiosit√† e la potenza drammatica dell'era barocca.

Programma:
H√§ndel: Sinfonia - Arrivo della Regina di Saba (da Salomone)
H√§ndel: Zadok il Sacerdote (Inno dell'Incoronazione n. 1)
H√§ndel: Il Re Gioir√† (Inno dell'Incoronazione n. 3)
Bach: Concerto Brandeburghese n. 3
Bach: Ges√π, gioia del desiderio umano (dalla Cantata n. 147)
Vivaldi: Gloria in Re maggiore RV. 589

Questo sar√† l'ultimo concerto di Kevin Power, che si ritira dalla carica di direttore d'orchestra dopo oltre 50 anni di servizio con il coro. Un evento davvero speciale, da non perdere.

_source.productDescription:
Celebrate National Reconciliation Week 2025 at the Airlie Beach Foreshore on Saturday 31 May for the annual Welcome Whales event‚Äî an evening of culture, community and connection.

Kicking off from 4:30pm, Yooribaya Cultural Experiences will be onsite hosting interactive kids' activities and collaborative cultural art creation. Guests will be welcomed with a traditional Welcome to Country, followed by a Smoking Ceremony and traditional dance performances that pay tribute to the custodians of this land.

Learn about the incredible journey of the humpback whales as they return to the coastline, and cap off the evening by enjoying a free outdoor screening of the family favourite Free Willy on the big screen at 6:30pm.

This is a free, family-friendly event open to everyone. Bring your picnic rugs, invite your friends and join them in celebrating culture, reconciliation and the arrival of these magnificent creatures.

_source.productDescription:
Experience Summer Land Camels' breath-taking sunset views while sipping your favourite vodka cocktail right alongside the camels. This is an official Eat Local Month Event.

Graze your way through a platter featuring award-winning camel milk cheeses, charcuterie, and local produce. As the sun goes down, enjoy their legendary camel curry and save room for camel milk gelato for dessert!

During the evening, their CEO, Paul Martin, will take you on an engaging paddock-to-plate journey, sharing the story behind their  sustainable farming practices and the remarkable health benefits of camel milk. Gain unique insights into how they ethically craft their award-winning dairy, from farm to table, while preserving the natural environment and caring for our camels.

Includes:
A glass of sparkling wine on arrival
A grazing platter showcasing award-winning Camel Milk Cheeses and local charcuterie
A Camel Curry or Vegetarian Curry (Gluten Free options are also available)

Please note:
The grazing platter is designed to share entree-sized portions and will be served on one platter per table showcasing a selection of their award-winning Camel Milk Cheeses and local charcuterie.Drinks will be available for purchase, including cocktails, mocktails, vodka-tasting paddles, beer, wine and non-alcoholic options.

This event has sold out in previous years so invite some friends and grab your tickets so you don't miss out!

Ammirate il tramonto mozzafiato di Summer Land Camels sorseggiando il vostro cocktail preferito a base di vodka in compagnia dei cammelli. Questo √® un evento ufficiale del Mese del Mangiare Locale.

Sfogliate un piatto di formaggi a base di latte di cammello, salumi e prodotti locali pluripremiati. Al tramonto, gustate il loro leggendario curry di cammello e lasciate un po' di spazio per un gelato al latte di cammello come dessert!

Durante la serata, il loro CEO, Paul Martin, vi accompagner√† in un coinvolgente viaggio dal pascolo al piatto, raccontando la storia delle loro pratiche agricole sostenibili e i notevoli benefici per la salute del latte di cammello. Scoprite come producono eticamente il loro pluripremiato latticino, dalla fattoria alla tavola, preservando l'ambiente naturale e prendendosi cura dei nostri cammelli.

Include:
Un bicchiere di spumante all'arrivo
Un piatto unico con formaggi di latte di cammello pluripremiati e salumi locali
Un curry di cammello o un curry vegetariano (sono disponibili anche opzioni senza glutine)

Nota bene:
Il piatto unico √® pensato per condividere porzioni di portata principale e verr√† servito su un piatto per tavolo con una selezione dei loro formaggi di latte di cammello pluripremiati e salumi locali. Saranno disponibili bevande per l'acquisto, tra cui cocktail, analcolici, palette per la degustazione di vodka, birra, vino e opzioni analcoliche.

Questo evento ha registrato il tutto esaurito negli anni precedenti, quindi invitate gli amici e acquistate i biglietti per non perdervi l'occasione!
